author: darybannova
description: Меня просто от этого трясет🤬😤 Пришло тепло и мы все больше времени проводим на детской площадке. Чего там только не увидишь.. бываешь свидетелем каких-то ситуаций, но сегодня мы стали участниками одного прикола.  Песочница. Моя дочь играет с другой девочкой с лопаткой и машинкой, все хорошо. Вокруг много детей и все друг с другом общаются, играют и тд. Тут прибывает в это заведение еще один ребенок с мамой и идет в сторону, где играет моя дочь. Этот мальчик еще не разговаривает, за него все говорит мама. В общем он очень хотел подружиться с моей дочкой, подошел к ней и сел рядом, моя дочь помахала ему рукой и сказала: «привет, мальчик». Так как он пока не говорит, его мама сказала ему: «сынок, девочка говорит привет, помаши ей». Мальчик помахал дочке рукой, все улыбнулись, и, КАЗАЛОСЬ БЫ, ЧТО НЕ ТАК???  А дело в том, что мамочка этого мальчика решила, что этого не достаточно, и сказала своему сыну: «иди скорее, ПОЦЕЛУЙ девочку». Мальчик послушно встал и начал пытаться поцеловать мою дочь!!! Совершенно чужие для нас люди! Мне в эту же секунду стало плохо и я вежливо попросила этого не делать.  Зачем??? Для чего вы учите ребенка подходить к незнакомым детям и ЦЕЛОВАТЬ ИХ??? Не просто поздороваться, помахать, не обнять в конце концов, а ПОЦЕЛОВАТЬ!!!  Блин, ну это же нарушение всего вообще!! От гигиены до личного пространства. Неужели это кому-то нужно объяснять??  Пожалуйста, скажите, что я не одна такая, кто считает это дикостью… #дети #жизнь #семья #дочь #треш #площадка #мамскийблог #мама #мамаидочь #история #истории #лето

author: richardakers27
description: Ozzy Osbourne, born John Michael Osbourne on December 3, 1948, in Birmingham, England, is a pioneering figure in heavy metal music, renowned for his distinctive voice, charismatic stage presence, and tumultuous career. Often referred to as the "Prince of Darkness," Osbourne has had a profound influence on rock music and popular culture, both as the frontman of Black Sabbath and as a solo artist. Osbourne's early life was marked by economic hardship and a rebellious spirit. Growing up in a working-class family in Birmingham, he faced numerous challenges, including a troubled academic career and a series of odd jobs. His passion for music emerged during his teenage years, and he eventually joined the band Earth, which would later become Black Sabbath. In 1968, Black Sabbath was formed with Osbourne as the lead vocalist, alongside guitarist Tony Iommi, bassist Geezer Butler, and drummer Bill Ward. The band's self-titled debut album, released in 1970, is often credited with pioneering heavy metal music. Black Sabbath's dark, heavy sound and Osbourne's distinctive voice set the stage for a new genre and influenced countless bands that followed. Black Sabbath's 1970 release, "Paranoid," further cemented their place in rock history with iconic tracks like "Iron Man," "War Pigs," and the title track "Paranoid." The album's success solidified Osbourne's reputation as a leading figure in the heavy metal genre. His theatrical stage presence and powerful vocals became defining characteristics of the band's performances. Despite the band's success, Osbourne's tenure with Black Sabbath was marked by internal conflicts and his own struggles with substance abuse. The pressures of fame and the lifestyle associated with it took a toll on Osbourne, leading to his departure from the band in 1979. His departure was a significant turning point, both for him and for Black Sabbath, who continued to have success with different lineups. In 1980, Ozzy Osbourne launched his solo career with the release of "Blizzard of Ozz," an album that introduced a new chapter in his career. The album featured hit songs like "Crazy Train" and "Mr. Crowley," showcasing Osbourne's ability to blend melodic elements with his heavy metal roots. The success of the album marked the beginning of Osbourne's successful solo career and established him as a major force in rock music. Osbourne's solo career continued to thrive throughout the 1980s and 1990s with a series of successful albums, including "Diary of a Madman" (1981) and "No More Tears" (1991). His music during this period maintained his heavy metal edge while also exploring new themes and styles. Hits like "Mama, I'm Coming Home" and "No More Tears" became staples of his live performances. Despite ongoing health issues and various personal challenges, including his battle with Parkinson's disease, Osbourne has continued to tour and record new music. His influence on heavy metal and rock music remains significant, and his contributions to the genre have been recognized with numerous awards and honors. Ozzy Osbourne's impact on music and culture is profound. He is often credited with shaping the sound of heavy metal and influencing countless artists who have followed in his footsteps. His career, marked by both remarkable achievements and notable controversies, has established him as one of rock's most enduring and iconic figures. Overall, Ozzy Osbourne's legacy is characterized by his innovative approach to heavy metal, his larger-than-life persona, and his ability to connect with audiences through his music and performances. author: alswithsalym
description: It sounds strange, maybe even morbid. But living with ALS means facing things most people never have to think about like what photo will be used when I’m gone. Recently ish took mine last November  There’s a peace in it. It’s the photo I chose. Not one picked in a rush, not a random old memory. It’s me, now, present, real. It means my loved ones won’t have to make that choice through tears. But it also broke my heart as I silently smiled through the tears I was swallowing so no one can see the pain.  No one should have to do this. No one should have to look into a lens and wonder how long that photo will outlive them. But here I am and somehow, taking control of that one small thing gave me back a little dignity in a disease that takes so much. This isn’t giving up. This is love I have for myself, for my people, for the story I leave behind. #ALS #livingwithals  #obituaryphoto #thisisals #griefandhealing #alsawareness #alscaregiver #alsadvocate #alsawarenessmonth #alsadvocacy #viral

author: foodwithbearhands
description: Korean BBQ Shotgun Shells 😮‍💨 Recipe ⤵️⤵️⤵️ Before we dive into the recipe, I’ve got to give a shoutout to @Bearmountain BBQ —I’ve been using their pellets for the past five years, and there is a reason I do! Their smoke pellets add incredible depth and flavor to everything I cook. For this one, I’m using one of my NEW go-to blends: Old Fashioned Pellets! Shotgun Shell Ingredients: 1 Pack Manicotti (14 Shells) 1 Pack Bacon 1 lb Ground Beef 1 lb Ground Pork 1 Bunch Green Onions 1/4 Cup Canned Carrots 4 Tbsp Soy Sauce 1 Tbsp Sesame Oil 1 Tbsp Chili Oil 2 Tbsp Gochujang 2 Garlic Cloves 1 Tbsp Ginger 3 Tbsp BBQ Rub (Grilling with Dad-All Purpose) 4 Tbsp BBQ Sauce How to: 1. Add Ground Beef, Pork, Green Onions, Carrots, Soy Sauce, Sesame Oil, Chili Oil, Gochujang, Garlic, Ginger in a bowl and mix well 2. Add Mixture to a ziplock piping bag 3. Add mixture in Manicotti Shells and wrap with regular bacon (NOT THICK) 4. Refrigerate overnight or for 3-4 hours 5. Add your favorite BBQ rub  6. In the Smoker at 325 degrees for 45 min 7. Then add bbq sauce and let that set for 10-15 minutes or until bacon is cooked 8. Garnish with Spicy Korean Mayo, Green Onions, and Sesame Seeds Spicy Korean Mayo Ingredients: 1/2 Cup Mayo 2 Tbsp Gochujang 2 Tbsp Honey 1 Lemon How to ➡️ add ingredients in a bowl and whisk it’s that easy 😮‍💨 Smoker: @Weber Grills SearWood BBQ Rub: @Grillin With Dad  Knife: Bear Hands Cleaver @THE COOKING GUILD  Shirt: @Poncho  #korean #bbq #shotgun #shells #recipe

description: Trump Issues Final Death Blow To Harvard & America #usa #america  The Government is forcing Harvard to kick out all of its foreign students and they will no longer allow them to admit foreign students. They’re also threatening to do the same to any other university that defies Trump. This is the latest escalation from Trump as the White House tries to force the private university into capitulating to him and letting him control it. Harvard has called Trump’s actions illegal. Others have called it authoritarianism. This comes as he keeps stripping research funding from Harvard preventing them from creating cures for cancer and other deadly diseases. 27% of students at Harvard are international students, and they paid more than American students. This enabled Harvard to allow poor Americans to attend the university for free. This will strip those smart kids from poor families to lose their education and it will cause America, like Germany in the 1930s, to lose its best scientists, students, and no longer be considered the international destination for academic excellence. Harvard will be suing Trump again over this as they enter into, not just a fight for their life, but also a fight for Americans to have the right to free thought and speech. Guys, America had the cheat codes. We took the smartest people from all over the world, taught them at our universities and connected them to capital, and then they formed businesses here or they joined our national research efforts to help us build the atomic bomb, go to the moon, or create the internet. America will now be dumber, poorer, and less safe.
